      "body": "**Cargo spacecraft** are [robotic spacecraft](openitem:fb1ncQOXqr) that are designed to carry cargo, possibly to support space stations' operation by transporting food, propellant and other supplies. This is different from space probes, whose missions are to conduct scientific investigations.\n\nAutomated cargo spacecraft have been used since 1978 and have serviced Salyut 6, Salyut 7, Mir, the International Space Station and Tiangong space laboratory.",
      "source": "Remixed excerpt from https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cargo_spacecraft licensed under CC BY-SA 3.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/)."
