      "title": "Melanie Brown (Mel B)",
      "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/17/Mel_B_New_York_2017.jpg",
      "body": '''
**Melanie Janine Brown** [MBE](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Order_of_the_British_Empire "Order of the British Empire") (born 29 May 1975;[\[2\]](#cite_note-MTV-2) known as **Melanie B** and **Mel B**) is an English singer, actress, and television personality. She rose to fame in the 1990s as a member of the girl group [Spice Girls](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spice_Girls "Spice Girls"), in which she was nicknamed **Scary Spice**. With over 100 million records sold worldwide,[\[3\]](#cite_note-3) the group became the [best-selling female group of all time](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_best-selling_girl_groups "List of best-selling girl groups").

During the Spice Girls hiatus, Mel B released her debut solo album, _[Hot](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hot_(Mel_B_album) "Hot (Mel B album)")_ (2000). The album's lead single, "[I Want You Back](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I_Want_You_Back_(Mel_B_song) "I Want You Back (Mel B song)")", reached number one on the [UK Singles Chart](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UK_Singles_Chart "UK Singles Chart"), and was included on the soundtrack for the 1998 film _[Why Do Fools Fall in Love](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Why_Do_Fools_Fall_in_Love_(film) "Why Do Fools Fall in Love (film)")_. Other singles from the album, such as "[Tell Me](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tell_Me_(Mel_B_song) "Tell Me (Mel B song)")" and "[Feels So Good](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Feels_So_Good_(Mel_B_song) "Feels So Good (Mel B song)")", both reached the top 5 in the UK charts. After signing with the [independent label](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Independent_record_label "Independent record label") Amber Café, she released her second solo album, _[L.A. State of Mind](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L.A._State_of_Mind "L.A. State of Mind")_ (2005), which spawned a single, "[Today](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Today_(Mel_B_song) "Today (Mel B song)")". Mel B released "[For Once in My Life](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/For_Once_in_My_Life_(Mel_B_song) "For Once in My Life (Mel B song)")" in 2013, her first single in eight years; it peaked at No. 2 on the [_Billboard_ Hot Dance Club Songs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dance_Club_Songs "Dance Club Songs") chart.[\[4\]](#cite_note-4)

More at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mel_B
''',
