The **Tesla Model S** is a [battery-powered](openitem:battery-powered) - [wiki:battery-powered](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battery_electric_vehicle "Battery electric vehicle") [liftback](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liftback "Liftback") car produced by [Tesla, Inc.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tesla,_Inc. "Tesla, Inc.") It was introduced on June 22, 2012,[\[9\]](#cite_note-MSlaunch4-9) and is positioned as Tesla's flagship model.

In 2013, the Model S became the first electric car to top the monthly new-car-sales ranking in any country, leading twice in Norway, in September and December 2013[\[10\]](#cite_note-SalesNorway09201322-10)[\[11\]](#cite_note-NorwayTop122-11)[\[12\]](#cite_note-NorwayTop222-12)[\[13\]](#cite_note-NorwayTop322-13) and in Denmark in December 2015.[\[14\]](#cite_note-Denmark201522-14) Sales passed 250,000 units in September 2018.[\[15\]](#cite_note-ModelS200k-15)[\[16\]](#cite_note-Tesla1Q2018-16)[\[17\]](#cite_note-Tesla2Q2018-17)[\[18\]](#cite_note-Tesla3Q2018-18) The Model S was the top-selling [plug-in electric car](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plug-in_electric_car "Plug-in electric car") worldwide in 2015 and 2016, although it was later surpassed by the [Model 3](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tesla_Model_3 "Tesla Model 3").[\[19\]](#cite_note-US2016record-19)[\[20\]](#cite_note-Top10PEVs2016-20)[\[21\]](#cite_note-Top30PEVs20163-21)

In an early review of the Model S, _[Consumer Reports](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_Reports "Consumer Reports")_ declared, "This car performs better than anything we've ever tested before. Let me repeat that: Not just the best _electric_ car, but the best car. It does just about everything really, really well."[\[22\]](#cite_note-22) In their Owner Satisfaction survey owners have consistently rated Teslas at, or near, the top rankings.[\[23\]](#cite_note-23) In 2019, _[Motor Trend](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motor_Trend "Motor Trend")_ named the 2013 Tesla Model S the ultimate "Car of the Year" over the magazine's entire 70-year history.[\[24\]](#cite_note-UltimateCar3-24) It received a refresh in June 2021.

See more https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tesla_Model_S
